WEBVTT

00:00:01.419 --> 00:00:07.419
We warmly welcome all of you to JW Broadcasting.

00:00:07.419 --> 00:00:13.419
This month's theme is imitate Jehovah's generosity.

00:00:13.419 --> 00:00:18.420
Our program will bring us closer to our great God, Jehovah.

00:00:18.420 --> 00:00:20.420
Here's a sample.

00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:23.420
What will you do in paradise?

00:00:23.420 --> 00:00:27.420
Some of our young ones share what they look forward to in the New World

00:00:27.420 --> 00:00:32.420
and how their hope draws them to Jehovah.

00:00:32.420 --> 00:00:39.420
The Book of Hosea can teach us profound truths if we know how to find them.

00:00:39.420 --> 00:00:47.420
We'll explore Hosea together and learn how to dig for our own treasures.

00:00:47.420 --> 00:00:59.420
You Christian sisters are beautiful examples of compassion, self-sacrifice, humility, and so much more.

00:00:59.420 --> 00:01:05.420
But at times some of you may feel that others don't notice what you do.

00:01:05.420 --> 00:01:15.420
This month's music video will assure you that your brothers and sisters love and appreciate you very much.

00:01:15.420 --> 00:01:22.420
There's much to look forward to in this edition of JW Broadcasting.

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:46.730
Humans are born with a strong inclination to imitate.

00:01:46.730 --> 00:01:52.730
In fact, very young infants have been observed imitating facial expressions.

00:01:52.730 --> 00:01:54.730
That's amazing.

00:01:54.730 --> 00:02:01.730
Makes me think of an experience I had some 40 years ago when Susan and I were in the circuit work.

00:02:01.730 --> 00:02:12.729
A sister told me that her little five-year-old son was looking in a mirror and making various expressions with his face and eyes.

00:02:12.729 --> 00:02:15.729
His mother asked, what are you doing?

00:02:15.729 --> 00:02:20.729
He said, I can't do like brother let.

00:02:20.729 --> 00:02:23.729
I'll never be a circuit overseer.

00:02:23.729 --> 00:02:32.979
Well, I'm sure he soon learned that voluminous facial expressions are not a requirement for circuit work.

00:02:32.979 --> 00:02:36.979
In fact, they could be a disadvantage.

00:02:36.979 --> 00:02:42.979
By the way, thank you for putting up with me all these years.

00:02:42.979 --> 00:02:48.979
But how does a small child learn to walk, feed himself and talk?

00:02:48.979 --> 00:02:52.979
He learns by imitating his parents and others.

00:02:52.979 --> 00:03:00.979
However, there's one type of imitating that does not come automatically or even easily.

00:03:00.979 --> 00:03:04.979
It's identified at Ephesians 5.1.

00:03:04.979 --> 00:03:12.979
It says, therefore, become imitators of God as beloved children.

00:03:12.979 --> 00:03:14.979
Notice the word become.

00:03:14.979 --> 00:03:18.979
We are not born as imitators of God.

00:03:18.979 --> 00:03:26.979
Because of inherited imperfection, we aren't even born with an inclination to become an imitator of God.

00:03:26.979 --> 00:03:35.979
Genesis 8.21 says, for the inclination of the heart of man is bad from his youth up.

00:03:35.979 --> 00:03:41.979
Therefore, it takes earnest effort to become an imitator of God.

00:03:41.979 --> 00:03:46.979
But it's well worth the effort and Jehovah will help us.

00:03:46.979 --> 00:03:53.979
What blessings will we personally read if we become an imitator of God?

00:03:53.979 --> 00:04:02.979
The greatest blessing, Jehovah will see that we are trying to be like Him and He will love us and draw close to us.

00:04:02.979 --> 00:04:13.979
Also, the more we learn about Jehovah and strive to be like Him, the more we'll love Him and the closer we'll draw to Him.

00:04:13.979 --> 00:04:19.980
Cultivating Godly qualities will result in improved relations with others.

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:24.980
Imitating Godly qualities will make us a better person overall.

00:04:24.980 --> 00:04:30.980
The more we like Jehovah, the happier we'll be.

00:04:30.980 --> 00:04:32.980
That's how He created us.

00:04:32.980 --> 00:04:41.980
Those are just a few of the blessings we'll reap if we become an imitator of God.

00:04:41.980 --> 00:04:50.980
In our publications, more than 40 different qualities of Jehovah have been identified and discussed.

00:04:50.980 --> 00:04:54.980
But in this discussion, let's examine just one.

00:04:54.980 --> 00:05:01.980
We'll discuss the theme, imitate Jehovah's generosity.

00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:06.980
Generosity is an aspect of Jehovah's love.

00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:13.980
Unquestionably, Jehovah God is the most generous giver in the universe.

00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:15.980
Let's talk about this.

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:20.980
Eons and eons ago, Jehovah God was all alone.

00:05:20.980 --> 00:05:30.980
And even though it's impossible for us to comprehend, He wasn't lonely or lacking anything, but because of love.

00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:36.980
He generously chose to share the gift of life with others.

00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:40.980
He decided to become a father, a creator.

00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:48.980
Logically, He began by creating a son with whom He could directly enjoy fellowship.

00:05:48.980 --> 00:05:54.980
As we know, this son became known as the Word, as Jehovah's spokesman.

00:05:55.980 --> 00:06:03.980
But then, at some point in time, again, not because of loneliness or lacking anything, but because of love.

00:06:03.980 --> 00:06:15.980
He chose to further expand his family by creating millions of angelic sons who could also directly associate with him.

00:06:16.980 --> 00:06:25.980
Then amazingly, further down the stream of time, because of love, He again chose to expand his family.

00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:33.980
These children were a lower form of life, but ones who were made in His image, and whom He loved deeply.

00:06:33.980 --> 00:06:36.980
Of course, we're talking about Adam and Eve.

00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:40.980
The original parents of all of us.

00:06:40.980 --> 00:06:46.980
If Jehovah had not created them, none of us would ever have been born.

00:06:46.980 --> 00:06:54.980
Yes, life itself is a wonderful, miraculous, and generous gift.

00:06:54.980 --> 00:07:01.980
Without this gift, we wouldn't be able to enjoy any of Jehovah's other marvelous blessings.

00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:08.980
Let's now talk about Jehovah's generosity when it comes to physical gifts.

00:07:09.980 --> 00:07:15.980
Every good gift and every perfect present is from above.

00:07:15.980 --> 00:07:19.980
Think for a moment about the planet we live on.

00:07:19.980 --> 00:07:25.980
Jehovah created the earth as a beautiful and unique home for us.

00:07:25.980 --> 00:07:37.980
It has all the right conditions to sustain life, including the oxygen and water cycles that continually recycle essential resources.

00:07:39.980 --> 00:07:47.980
If the earth were closer to the sun, all the water would boil off, and the planet would be a barren rock.

00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:58.980
Conversely, if it were farther from the sun, the water would freeze, and the planet would be like an uninhabitable iceberg.

00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:08.980
Jehovah placed the earth at the perfect location, often called the Goldilocks Zone.

00:08:08.980 --> 00:08:13.980
Think too about the marvelous gift of our human bodies.

00:08:13.980 --> 00:08:22.980
Even in our imperfect state, as mentioned at Psalm 139.14, we are wonderfully made.

00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:30.980
Isn't it brilliant how our skin is designed to heal when we cut, scrape, or bruise it?

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:34.980
When we scratch, scrape, or dent our car.

00:08:34.980 --> 00:08:36.980
Does it heal itself?

00:08:36.980 --> 00:08:45.980
Can you imagine what we would look like if every time we damage our skin, it just stayed that way?

00:08:45.980 --> 00:08:50.980
We'd begin to look pretty rough in just a short period of time.

00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:59.980
And isn't it amazing how the skin allows water to exit the body in the form of perspiration?

00:08:59.980 --> 00:09:06.980
But at the same time, it doesn't allow water to enter the body when we take a bath.

00:09:06.980 --> 00:09:10.980
Otherwise, we'd become waterlogged.

00:09:10.980 --> 00:09:19.980
Ponder for a moment about how food is not only nutritious, but it's also delicious.

00:09:20.980 --> 00:09:24.980
This makes fueling our bodies very enjoyable.

00:09:24.980 --> 00:09:35.980
Jehovah could have made eating like putting gasoline in a car on necessary function, but void of enjoyment.

00:09:35.980 --> 00:09:41.980
Think of all the tasty varieties of food as just one example.

00:09:41.980 --> 00:09:45.980
How many varieties of grapes are there?

00:09:45.980 --> 00:09:54.980
According to the Food and Agriculture Organization, there are about 10,000 different great varieties worldwide.

00:09:54.980 --> 00:10:01.980
Jehovah could have given us just two varieties, red and green.

00:10:01.980 --> 00:10:05.980
But why do we have some 10,000 varieties?

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:10.980
Because of Jehovah's voluminous generosity.

00:10:11.980 --> 00:10:19.980
But now we ask, how can we imitate Jehovah's generosity in giving physical gifts?

00:10:19.980 --> 00:10:29.980
It's obvious that Jehovah's put a lot of thought into his gift giving so that his gifts are practical and beneficial.

00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:35.980
Likewise, we should prayerfully meditate so that our gifts are useful.

00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:40.980
Not all gifts are practical. One brother gave this example.

00:10:40.980 --> 00:10:46.980
A puppy might make a fine gift to a young one living in a rural setting.

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:49.980
But it's a terrible gift to a Bethelite.

00:10:49.980 --> 00:11:03.419
If our brother lacks food, clothing or shelter, we don't just say, go in peace, keep warm and well fed.

00:11:03.419 --> 00:11:17.419
No, we apply Proverbs 3.27, which says, do not withhold good from those to whom you should give it if it is within your power to help.

00:11:17.419 --> 00:11:28.419
In addition to helping brothers in need directly, we can indirectly help them by making donations to the worldwide work.

00:11:29.419 --> 00:11:50.419
The governing body prayerfully strives to use wisely these precious dedicated funds to help our dear brothers who have been afflicted by natural or man-made disasters and who urgently need suitable kingdom halls and assistance in many other ways.

00:11:50.419 --> 00:11:58.419
Speaking of the need for kingdom halls as just one example, please look at these pictures from the Philippines.

00:11:58.419 --> 00:12:04.419
Here are six before and after photographs.

00:12:04.419 --> 00:12:14.419
And what do you think was the individual average cost of these six new simplified but dignified kingdom halls?

00:12:14.419 --> 00:12:18.419
$21,000 US dollars.

00:12:19.419 --> 00:12:21.419
Please think about this.

00:12:21.419 --> 00:12:28.419
Jehovah's physical gifts such as the rain, sunshine and oxygen are recurring.

00:12:28.419 --> 00:12:33.419
What's one way to imitate this aspect of Jehovah's giving?

00:12:33.419 --> 00:12:46.419
Well, 1 Corinthians 162 says, on the first day of every week each of you should set something aside according to his own means.

00:12:46.419 --> 00:12:59.419
In harmony with the scriptural principle many have chosen to set something aside each month by scheduling recurring online donations.

00:12:59.419 --> 00:13:06.419
But now let's briefly contemplate Jehovah's spiritual gifts which are even more impressive.

00:13:07.419 --> 00:13:09.419
Think about the Bible.

00:13:09.419 --> 00:13:12.419
Where would we be without it?

00:13:12.419 --> 00:13:16.419
Lost, hopeless, floundering.

00:13:16.419 --> 00:13:21.419
We'd have to learn by experience, the school of hard knocks.

00:13:21.419 --> 00:13:25.419
We'd need at least two lives to live.

00:13:25.419 --> 00:13:31.419
One to practice and the second to perform.

00:13:31.419 --> 00:13:34.419
Next, think about the Holy Spirit.

00:13:34.419 --> 00:13:41.419
John 1426 describes it as a helper, teacher and a remembranceer.

00:13:41.419 --> 00:13:48.419
It is the most powerful force in the universe and Jehovah gives it to us generously.

00:13:48.419 --> 00:13:52.419
Consider for a moment the resurrection hope.

00:13:52.419 --> 00:13:59.419
It strengthens us in time of great distress when death takes a loved one.

00:13:59.419 --> 00:14:02.419
Or when we face death ourselves.

00:14:02.419 --> 00:14:06.419
I'm reminded of the six-year-old girl who said,

00:14:06.419 --> 00:14:10.419
thank you, Jehovah, for the resurrection hope.

00:14:10.419 --> 00:14:14.419
It is a very good idea.

00:14:14.419 --> 00:14:21.419
For a final example, what was Jehovah's greatest spiritual gift of generosity?

00:14:21.419 --> 00:14:27.419
The gift of his son to purchase us from sin and death.

00:14:27.419 --> 00:14:31.419
And it wasn't just any angel whom Jehovah sent.

00:14:31.419 --> 00:14:36.419
It was his firstborn, his only begotten son.

00:14:36.419 --> 00:14:44.419
What if you were tied to a chair and forced to watch the torture and execution of your most beloved child?

00:14:44.419 --> 00:14:47.419
That would be horrible.

00:14:47.419 --> 00:14:53.419
Of course, Jehovah was not tied, but because of his great love for us.

00:14:53.419 --> 00:15:01.419
He restrained himself and allowed the torture and execution of his most precious son.

00:15:01.419 --> 00:15:07.419
That is the ultimate example of generosity.

00:15:07.419 --> 00:15:15.419
But now we ask, how can we imitate Jehovah's generosity in giving spiritual gifts?

00:15:15.419 --> 00:15:20.419
One way, by being generous and giving sincere commendation.

00:15:20.419 --> 00:15:25.419
If you see something good, say something good.

00:15:25.419 --> 00:15:28.419
Proverbs 15, 23 says,

00:15:28.419 --> 00:15:34.419
a word spoken at the right time how good it is.

00:15:34.419 --> 00:15:37.419
Words have great power.

00:15:37.419 --> 00:15:44.419
To illustrate, think of how two words from a convention chairman can lift thousands of pounds.

00:15:44.419 --> 00:15:46.419
What are they?

00:15:46.419 --> 00:15:49.419
Please stand.

00:15:49.419 --> 00:15:53.419
In this vein, Proverbs 1821 says,

00:15:53.419 --> 00:15:58.419
death and life are in the power of the tongue.

00:15:58.419 --> 00:16:04.419
Just a few words at the right time can make a tremendous difference in a person's life.

00:16:04.419 --> 00:16:12.419
They can cause a depressed one to stand with a positive hope for the future.

00:16:12.419 --> 00:16:16.419
Another way, freely give out forgiveness.

00:16:16.419 --> 00:16:27.419
Colossians 313 reminds us that Jehovah freely forgives us and that we must also do the same.

00:16:27.419 --> 00:16:34.419
The word freely in English means generously and can also mean without charge.

00:16:34.419 --> 00:16:41.419
Is there someone you can extend true forgiveness to in imitation of our generous God?

00:16:41.419 --> 00:16:47.419
Additionally, how about generously giving out knowledge?

00:16:47.419 --> 00:16:56.419
Do we pray for a Bible study and then work in harmony with those prayers by searching diligently for a deserving one?

00:16:56.419 --> 00:17:06.420
Do we liberally train others and share the skills we have in the ministry and in the maintenance and construction of theocratic facilities?

00:17:07.420 --> 00:17:14.420
People in general often hoard the knowledge they have in order to protect their job.

00:17:14.420 --> 00:17:22.420
But like Jehovah, we gladly share the knowledge we have with others.

00:17:22.420 --> 00:17:32.420
During our discussion, we barely scratch the surface regarding Jehovah's generosity and how we can imitate Him.

00:17:32.420 --> 00:17:40.420
We will learn forever about our great God and how we can better reflect His qualities.

00:17:40.420 --> 00:17:55.420
But in the meantime, the more we learn about Him and the more closely we can imitate Him, the richer, happier and more satisfying our lives will be.

00:17:55.420 --> 00:18:02.720
And why? Because that's how He created us.

00:18:02.720 --> 00:18:09.720
Another way we imitate Jehovah's generosity is by showing hospitality.

00:18:09.720 --> 00:18:12.720
Do you sometimes hold back?

00:18:12.720 --> 00:18:17.720
Our next segment offers practical suggestions that can help you.

00:18:17.720 --> 00:18:30.420
What mattered most to me was that everything was just right.

00:18:30.420 --> 00:18:37.420
My apartment had to be spotless and the dining table had to be full with different types of food, completely full.

00:18:38.420 --> 00:18:45.420
I was worried that our apartment wasn't big enough to accommodate guests, not even for a meal.

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:52.420
I was often wondering if we would have enough time for invitations or if it would be too stressful.

00:18:52.420 --> 00:18:58.420
Before my financial situation was much better, currently it's not good, but I manage.

00:18:58.420 --> 00:19:05.420
The brothers and sisters are such a precious gift from Jehovah. This is truly the family He gave us.

00:19:05.420 --> 00:19:11.420
The brothers and sisters have shown us so much love, and I want to do all I can to express my gratitude.

00:19:11.420 --> 00:19:15.420
The best way to do so is just by spending time together.

00:19:15.420 --> 00:19:18.420
We're happy to take time for our brothers.

00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:24.420
So many of the friends live alone or just want someone to spend time with.

00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:30.420
It's nice when we can show hospitality in our homes, but I've learned that hospitality starts in the Kingdom Hall.

00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:34.420
After all, Jehovah has invited all of us to be his guests.

00:19:34.420 --> 00:19:39.420
I prefer to stand right by the entrance. This way I can notice any interested ones that come to the meetings.

00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:45.420
A warm smile shows personal interest, and lets them know I'm genuinely happy that they've come.

00:19:45.420 --> 00:19:51.420
Brothers and sisters in the congregation are my family. That is why I want to hug them.

00:19:51.420 --> 00:19:56.420
Kiss them, ask them how they feel. They should feel happy just as I am.

00:19:57.420 --> 00:20:04.420
I am normally pretty tired after the meeting. I've had a long day and still have the rest of the week ahead of me.

00:20:04.420 --> 00:20:09.420
But that is the case with the others too. Sometimes there are things they would like to share.

00:20:09.420 --> 00:20:14.420
Taking the time to listen to them can really make their day.

00:20:14.420 --> 00:20:17.420
I plan to invite four to five friends every other week.

00:20:17.420 --> 00:20:24.420
To my great joy my plan came true within a year and a half. Everyone was invited, and everyone came.

00:20:24.420 --> 00:20:29.420
Brothers usually ask me what to bring. I say, don't bring anything. Just your beautiful smile.

00:20:29.420 --> 00:20:33.420
And bring someone who you know very well, but who I don't know.

00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:40.420
There have been times after the meeting when we've said to each other, we just have to invite someone over.

00:20:40.420 --> 00:20:46.420
Then we go around asking people sometimes four or more until we find someone who has time.

00:20:46.420 --> 00:20:53.420
This has led to so many beautiful moments together. No one feels pressured or expects anything extravagant.

00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:57.420
Everyone is relaxed and it feels like a calm evening with family.

00:20:57.420 --> 00:21:04.500
One experience completely changed my view of hospitality.

00:21:04.500 --> 00:21:11.500
A friend of mine called me and said, hey, I'm close by. Do you have time? Can I come over?

00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:16.500
I thought, what am I supposed to cook? At that moment, the doorbell ring.

00:21:16.500 --> 00:21:23.500
My friend was already there. The only thing I could think of to cook was pasta with sauce.

00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:29.500
When we sat down to eat, my friend said to me, Stephanie, pasta is my favorite food.

00:21:29.500 --> 00:21:32.500
That was a great moment.

00:21:32.500 --> 00:21:36.500
I live a simple life. To host brothers, I need to spend some money.

00:21:36.500 --> 00:21:42.500
However, there are leaflets with special offers. I checked them to see what's discounted.

00:21:42.500 --> 00:21:47.880
The friends are happy, and I didn't spend a lot of money.

00:21:47.880 --> 00:21:52.880
We've had several brothers spend an ITM. They come for pioneer school, elder school,

00:21:52.880 --> 00:21:55.880
and other theocratic projects.

00:21:55.880 --> 00:22:01.880
It's so encouraging to see their positive attitude when they come home in the evenings.

00:22:01.880 --> 00:22:07.880
It's priceless. They're energized from the school and they have so many upbuilding thoughts.

00:22:07.880 --> 00:22:10.880
Their positivity is contagious.

00:22:10.880 --> 00:22:17.670
Our apartment isn't very big, so we wondered where our guests could sleep.

00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:21.670
We decided to turn the office into a guest room.

00:22:22.670 --> 00:22:29.670
We had to move the desk into our room, but now we have space for an air mattress for our guests to sleep on.

00:22:29.670 --> 00:22:31.670
It's a great solution.

00:22:31.670 --> 00:22:35.670
I take photos of my guests and stick them into my photo album.

00:22:35.670 --> 00:22:40.670
We live in such times when it's normal to get said sometimes. It happens to me too.

00:22:40.670 --> 00:22:44.670
My remedy for sadness is to take the photos, look at them.

00:22:44.670 --> 00:22:50.670
Remember our get-togethers, remember our laughter, remember the atmosphere we had, the experiences I heard.

00:22:50.670 --> 00:22:53.670
I meditate on them and that lives me up again.

00:22:53.670 --> 00:22:58.670
When I see how happy my guests are, it makes me truly happy.

00:22:58.670 --> 00:23:04.670
Spending time together not only strengthens our friendships with each other, but also with Jehovah as well.

00:23:04.670 --> 00:23:07.670
We live in such insecure times.

00:23:07.670 --> 00:23:11.670
We really don't know what life situations we will face next.

00:23:11.670 --> 00:23:15.670
Not only are we affected by these situations, but others are also.

00:23:15.670 --> 00:23:22.670
Making the best out of the time we have together helps to build friendships strong and meaningful friendships.

00:23:22.670 --> 00:23:26.670
There are so many different personalities in the congregation.

00:23:26.670 --> 00:23:31.670
And the time is coming when it will be essential for us to stick together.

00:23:31.670 --> 00:23:36.670
We will face more and more pressure in this system of things.

00:23:36.670 --> 00:23:44.670
But we will be ever more thankful for the friendships and the congregation that can help us to resist this pressure.

00:23:45.670 --> 00:24:06.710
Together we are stronger because we can all support and rely on each other.

00:24:06.710 --> 00:24:08.710
How timely!

00:24:08.710 --> 00:24:12.710
That same Watchtower article made this point.

00:24:12.710 --> 00:24:20.710
As pressures mount, we will need the deepest of love between us and our brothers and sisters.

00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:28.710
Yes, by generously extending hospitality, we strengthen the bonds of love among us.

00:24:29.710 --> 00:24:39.710
We need that close bond with our brothers and sisters, especially when we suffer a painful, unexpected tragedy.

00:24:39.710 --> 00:24:45.710
Marcella, Maite and Jackie faced such a crisis.

00:24:45.710 --> 00:24:54.710
As we hear their story, notice how their strong faith helped them and their family endure.

00:24:55.710 --> 00:24:59.710
